---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "BlueStar Appliance Repair Los Angeles | Open Burner & Infrared Broiler Specialists";
const description = "Expert BlueStar appliance repair in Los Angeles. Open burner ranges, infrared broilers, Primus/Platinum/Nova series — 25,000 BTU to 130 BTU Ultra-Low. American-made since 1880. Same-day service. Call (626) 376-4458.";
const phone = "(626) 376-4458";
const phoneRaw = "6263764458";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HomeAndConstructionBusiness",
  "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — BlueStar Specialist",
  "url": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brand-bluestar-appliance-repair/",
  "telephone": "+16263764458",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "Los Angeles",
    "addressRegion": "CA",
    "postalCode": "90001",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "areaServed": ["Los Angeles County", "Orange County", "Ventura County"],
  "priceRange": "$$",
  "openingHours": "Mo-Sa 08:00-20:00",
  "hasOfferCatalog": {
    "@type": "OfferCatalog",
    "name": "BlueStar Repair Services",
    "itemListElement": [
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Range Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Open Burner Service"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Infrared Broiler Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Wall Oven Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Refrigerator Repair"}},
      {"@type":"Offer","itemOffered":{"@type":"Service","name":"BlueStar Rangetop Repair"}}
    ]
  }
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does BlueStar appliance repair cost in Los Angeles?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Most BlueStar repairs run $175–$580. Open burner igniter replacement, temperature sensor, or door gasket work is on the lower end. Infrared broiler element, gas valve, or control board replacement runs higher. Diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed. Written flat-rate estimate before work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is BlueStar's open burner design and how does it affect service?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BlueStar uses open burners — the burner is exposed rather than sealed to the cooktop surface. Open burners deliver more heat (up to 25,000 BTU) because combustion isn't restricted by a sealed cap assembly. For service, open burners accumulate debris differently than sealed burners: food particles and grease can reach the burner ports directly. BlueStar burner ports require regular cleaning and specific port-clearing technique. Open burner igniters also use a star-shaped cap geometry requiring OEM igniter positioning."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair BlueStar's infrared broiler?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. BlueStar's infrared broiler uses a ceramic-element system that operates at far higher surface temperatures than standard radiant broilers — delivering restaurant-grade searing performance. The infrared ceramic element is the most common broiler failure. We service the full infrared broiler assembly including the ceramic element, gas circuit, and ignition system."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Where is BlueStar made?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BlueStar is manufactured in Reading, Pennsylvania by Prizer-Painter Stove Works — a company with roots going back to 1880. BlueStar is one of the very few remaining American-made professional range manufacturers. All BlueStar ranges are built in the Reading, PA factory."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can BlueStar ranges really be ordered in 750 colors?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. BlueStar offers over 750 color options for their ranges — the most customizable professional range in the residential market. These are custom powder-coat finishes applied to the range body and door. The color finish requires non-abrasive service protocols during any work near the range exterior — powder coat scratches differently than stainless steel."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the Ultra-Low simmer on BlueStar and what happens when it fails?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BlueStar's Ultra-Low simmer reaches 130 BTU — the lowest of any residential burner. It uses a valve that partially restricts gas flow to achieve this output. The most common Ultra-Low failure: the restriction valve sticks in the restricted position (burner won't go above a very low flame) or fails to restrict (burner holds higher than intended minimum flame). We service the Ultra-Low valve assembly independently from the main gas valve."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>

<style>
  :root {
    --red: #C8102E;
    --black: #0a0a0a;
    --gray: #f5f5f5;
    --border: #e2e2e2;
    --text: #1a1a1a;
    --muted: #6b6b6b;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  body { font-family: 'Barlow', 'Inter', system-ui, sans-serif; color: var(--text); }

  .top-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 8px 24px; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 13px; color: #fff; }
  .top-bar a { color: #fff; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }

  .hero { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px 64px; color: #fff; }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap: 48px; align-items: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .hero-title { font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.05; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.6; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 540px; }
  .hero-cta-group { display: flex; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .btn-secondary { display: inline-block; border: 1px solid #555; color: #ccc; padding: 14px 28px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .hero-badge-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
  .hero-badge { background: #161616; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; padding: 16px 18px; }
  .badge-num { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--red); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .badge-label { font-size: 12px; color: #888; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }

  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 14px 24px; }
  .trust-bar-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .trust-item::before { content: "✓ "; }

  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .section-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-num { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .section-title { font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 36px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .section-black .section-title { color: #fff; }
  .section-lead { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .section-black .section-lead { color: #999; }

  /* BTU range visual */
  .btu-bar { background: linear-gradient(to right, #1a3a6a 0%, #2a5ea5 20%, #e8a030 70%, #C8102E 100%); height: 8px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 16px 0 8px; }
  .btu-labels { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--muted); }

  /* Series grid */
  .series-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: #2a2a2a; border: 1px solid #2a2a2a; margin-top: 28px; }
  .series-card { background: #161616; padding: 20px 18px; }
  .series-name { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .series-btu { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .series-desc { font-size: 12px; color: #666; line-height: 1.55; }

  .tip-block { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); background: #fff8f8; padding: 18px 20px; margin: 32px 0; max-width: 760px; }
  .tip-label { font-size: 10px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .tip-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-usa { border-color: #2a5ea5; background: #f0f7ff; }
  .tip-usa .tip-label { color: #2a5ea5; }
  .tip-open { border-color: #c8820a; background: #fff8f0; }
  .tip-open .tip-label { color: #c8820a; }

  .services-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .service-card { background: #fff; padding: 28px 24px; }
  .service-icon { font-size: 28px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-name { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--text); }
  .service-desc { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .service-issues { font-size: 12px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .features-2col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  .features-list { list-style: none; }
  .features-list li { padding: 14px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid #2a2a2a; font-size: 15px; color: #ccc; display: flex; gap: 12px; }
  .features-list li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--red); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .problems-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 16px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .problem-card { border: 1px solid var(--border); background: #fff; padding: 20px; }
  .problem-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; color: var(--text); }
  .problem-cause { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .problem-tag { display: inline-block; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; padding: 3px 8px; color: #fff; }
  .tag-common { background: var(--red); }
  .tag-open { background: #c8820a; }
  .tag-broiler { background: #2a5ea5; }
  .tag-coastal { background: #2a7a2a; }

  .pricing-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; }
  .pricing-table th { background: var(--text); color: #fff; text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
  .pricing-table td { padding: 14px 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 14px; }
  .pricing-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
  .pricing-table tr:nth-child(even) td { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-range { font-weight: 700; color: var(--red); }

  .why-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr)); gap: 24px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .why-card { border-left: 3px solid var(--red); padding: 20px; background: #fff; }
  .why-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .why-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .why-desc { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }

  .reviews-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .review-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
  .review-stars { color: var(--red); font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .review-text { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .review-author { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); }

  .repairs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 32px; }
  .repair-item { background: #fff; padding: 24px; }
  .repair-appliance { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .repair-issue { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .repair-detail { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .repair-meta { margin-top: 12px; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 600; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  .faq-list { margin-top: 32px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-q { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-a { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--muted); max-width: 760px; }

  .nearby-grid { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 20px; }
  .nearby-chip { background: var(--gray); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 8px 14px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
  .nearby-chip:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }

  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); padding: 72px 24px; text-align: center; color: #fff; }
  .bottom-cta-title { font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .bottom-cta-title span { color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta-sub { font-size: 17px; color: #888; margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .cta-phone-large { display: inline-block; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 42px); font-weight: 900; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red); padding-bottom: 4px; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .hero-badge-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .features-2col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .series-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .trust-bar-inner { flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="top-bar">
  <span>Mon–Sat 8am–8pm · Los Angeles &amp; Southern California</span>
  <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`}>{phone}</a>
</div>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">BlueStar Appliance Repair — Los Angeles</div>
      <h1 class="hero-title">
        BlueStar Repair.<br/>
        <span>Open Burner. Infrared.</span><br/>
        American-Made.
      </h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        BlueStar has been made in Reading, Pennsylvania since 1880 — open burners that reach 25,000 BTU and drop to 130 BTU Ultra-Low simmer, the infrared broiler no other residential range offers, and 750 color options. We know open burner service. We know the star-shaped cap geometry. We know the infrared element.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-cta-group">
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
        <a href="/book/" class="btn-secondary">Book Online</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-badge-grid">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">Same</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Day Service</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">OEM</div>
        <div class="badge-label">BlueStar Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">90-Day</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Warranty</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <div class="badge-num">$89</div>
        <div class="badge-label">Diagnostic Fee</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="trust-bar">
  <div class="trust-bar-inner">
    <span class="trust-item">Licensed &amp; Insured · CSLB #1138898</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Open Burner Port Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Infrared Broiler Specialists</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Ultra-Low Simmer Valve Service</span>
    <span class="trust-item">Flat-Rate Written Estimate</span>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">01 — About BlueStar</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Open Burners. American-Made. 25,000 BTU to 130 BTU.</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">
      BlueStar is manufactured by Prizer-Painter Stove Works in Reading, Pennsylvania — a company with roots going back to 1880. It's one of a tiny handful of professional ranges still made entirely in the United States. The Reading factory produces every BlueStar range by hand, and the product reflects that: open burners that deliver commercial-kitchen power, an infrared broiler that creates restaurant-grade searing, and a BTU range wider than any other residential range — from 25,000 BTU on the power burner down to 130 BTU on the Ultra-Low simmer, all without turning off the flame.
    </p>
    <p class="section-lead">
      BlueStar's other defining characteristic is color: over 750 custom powder-coat options for the range body and door, making it the most customizable professional range in the residential market. An LA kitchen with a custom-colored BlueStar is a design statement — which is why these appliances attract serious cooks who are equally serious about their kitchen aesthetic. They deserve service that matches that seriousness.
    </p>

    <div style="margin: 28px 0 8px">
      <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px">BlueStar BTU Range — Widest in Residential</div>
      <div class="btu-bar"></div>
      <div class="btu-labels">
        <span>130 BTU Ultra-Low Simmer</span>
        <span>25,000 BTU Power Burner</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="series-grid" style="margin-top:24px">
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-name">Primus Series</div>
        <div class="series-btu">Up to 22,000 BTU · Ultra-Low 130 BTU</div>
        <div class="series-desc">BlueStar's professional entry range. Open burners, cast iron grates, convection oven. Available in 30", 36", and 48". Standard stainless or custom color option.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-name">Platinum Series</div>
        <div class="series-btu">Up to 25,000 BTU · Ultra-Low 130 BTU</div>
        <div class="series-desc">The flagship BlueStar. 25,000 BTU power burner, infrared broiler standard, dry heat convection oven, telescoping rack. The range serious chefs choose.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="series-card">
        <div class="series-name">Nova Series</div>
        <div class="series-btu">Up to 18,000 BTU · Ultra-Low 130 BTU</div>
        <div class="series-desc">BlueStar's more accessible configuration — slightly lower BTU, still open burner design with Ultra-Low simmer. Same American manufacturing quality as Platinum.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-usa" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🇺🇸 Made in Reading, PA — What It Means for Parts</div>
      <div class="tip-text">BlueStar's Reading, Pennsylvania manufacturing has a practical implication for LA service: US-sourced OEM parts move faster than European imports. When we need a specific BlueStar open burner component, igniter assembly, or infrared broiler element, we're sourcing from a domestic supply chain rather than waiting for Italian or German parts. Most BlueStar OEM parts arrive same-day or next-day in the LA market. The American manufacturing also means service documentation and technical specifications are in English and accessible through the domestic service network — not translated from German or Italian.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">02 — Services</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Every BlueStar Appliance We Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">All BlueStar series — Primus, Platinum, Nova — across all configurations. Same-day across Los Angeles County.</p>

    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔥</div>
        <div class="service-name">Open Burner Range Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar's open burners are the defining feature — and the primary service consideration. The star-shaped burner cap creates more contact points between flame and cookware but also creates specific debris accumulation patterns. Food particles and grease can reach the burner ports directly (no sealed cap to prevent it), and the star geometry requires specific port-clearing technique to fully restore gas flow. We clean and service open burner ports differently than sealed burner maintenance. Igniter geometry is also star-cap specific — OEM BlueStar igniters only.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: open burner port blockage · star-cap igniter failure · gas valve · Ultra-Low simmer valve · oven temperature · convection fan · door gasket · control board · coastal corrosion</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔆</div>
        <div class="service-name">Infrared Broiler Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar's infrared broiler is genuinely unique in the residential range market — a ceramic radiant element that operates at far higher surface temperatures than standard broilers, delivering restaurant-grade searing and crisping performance. The ceramic infrared element is the most common broiler failure: thermal shock from rapid temperature cycling degrades the ceramic over time. Infrared broiler service requires specific component knowledge — the ceramic element, gas circuit, and ignition system are all specific to the BlueStar infrared configuration.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: infrared ceramic element failure · ignition fault · temperature inconsistency · gas valve · thermal shock damage assessment · element replacement</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🌡️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Wall Oven Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar single and double wall ovens — gas and electric with convection. BlueStar's dry heat convection oven design circulates air without adding moisture, which home cooks and bakers value for specific cooking applications. The convection fan and temperature sensor are the most common wall oven failure points. BlueStar also offers a combination range oven + wall oven configuration that we service as a complete system.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: temperature sensor · convection fan · dry heat mode fault · door gasket · heating element · self-clean lock · control board · temperature calibration</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">✨</div>
        <div class="service-name">Custom Color Range Service</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar's 750+ color options mean many LA kitchens have a uniquely specified range finish. Custom powder-coat surfaces scratch and chip differently than stainless — the powder coat is harder than paint but more vulnerable to edge contact than brushed stainless. We apply protective covers to all color-finish panels before any service work and use non-abrasive cleaning agents exclusively. A chip on a custom Midnight Blue or French Red BlueStar is immediately visible and not repairable without a full panel respray.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">All standard repairs with powder-coat safe protocols — protective covers, non-abrasive tools, and visual finish inspection before and after every service visit.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">❄️</div>
        <div class="service-name">Refrigerator Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar's refrigerator line — column and French door configurations added to complement the range lineup. BlueStar refrigerators use a standard sealed system platform with specific component configurations. As with any premium column refrigerator in a custom kitchen, we check installation clearances for condenser ventilation before any sealed system diagnosis. BlueStar refrigerators are a newer addition to the brand's lineup and parts availability continues to improve through the domestic supply chain.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: not cooling · condenser service · clearance check · door gasket · temperature sensor · ice maker · water dispenser · compressor · defrost system</div>
      </div>

      <div class="service-card">
        <div class="service-icon">🔩</div>
        <div class="service-name">Rangetop &amp; Cooktop Repair</div>
        <div class="service-desc">BlueStar rangetops — freestanding or built-in cooktop configurations with the same open burner system as the full ranges. Rangetops in custom island installations accumulate debris from all sides rather than just the front, which affects burner port maintenance frequency. We service BlueStar rangetops with the same open burner port protocol as the full range line.</div>
        <div class="service-issues">Common: open burner port blockage · igniter failure · gas valve · Ultra-Low simmer valve · island installation debris accumulation · coastal corrosion</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="tip-block tip-open" style="margin-top:32px">
      <div class="tip-label">🔥 Open Burner vs Sealed Burner — What the Service Difference Means</div>
      <div class="tip-text">BlueStar's open burners are fundamentally different from the sealed burners used on Wolf, Viking, Thermador, and most other premium brands. Sealed burners have a cap assembly that prevents debris from reaching the burner head — grease and food particles can only enter the burner from the sides. Open burners have direct access to the star-shaped cap from above — debris lands directly on the burner ports during cooking. The result: open burners deliver more heat but require more frequent port cleaning to maintain performance. We clean all open burner ports during every BlueStar range service call, regardless of whether it was the stated complaint — because partially blocked ports often affect performance subtly before causing obvious failure.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-black">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">03 — Technology</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">BlueStar Engineering — What Makes It Different to Service</h2>
    <p class="section-lead">BlueStar's open burner philosophy creates specific service requirements that sealed-burner experience doesn't prepare you for.</p>

    <div class="features-2col">
      <ul class="features-list">
        <li><strong>Star-Shaped Open Burner Cap</strong> — BlueStar's distinctive star-shaped burner cap distributes flame in a pattern that creates more even heating across the cookware bottom. The star geometry creates 8–12 gas ports in a circular pattern. When ports clog (the most common BlueStar range issue), the clogging is asymmetric — certain points of the star block while others remain clear, creating uneven flames before the burner fails completely. We test each port individually during open burner service.</li>
        <li><strong>Infrared Ceramic Broiler Element</strong> — The infrared element operates at 1,500–1,800°F surface temperature during use — far beyond the 700–900°F of a standard radiant broiler. This thermal load creates specific wear: the ceramic element develops micro-fractures from repeated thermal cycling before developing visible cracks. We inspect the infrared element visually at 400% magnification during every BlueStar broiler service call — catching micro-fracture progression before complete failure.</li>
        <li><strong>Ultra-Low Simmer Valve</strong> — Reaching 130 BTU requires a dedicated restriction valve that partially closes the gas supply path. This valve operates in its most restricted position far more often than any other position — holding the flame at 130 BTU for slow braises and sauces that can run for hours. The restriction mechanism wears from this sustained use, gradually losing its minimum restriction (simmer creeps higher) or sticking in restriction (burner won't go above simmer). We service the Ultra-Low valve assembly as a separate unit from the main gas valve.</li>
        <li><strong>Dry Heat Convection</strong> — BlueStar's convection system uses a fan without an additional heating element — circulating ambient oven heat rather than adding heated air. This dry heat convection produces specific results (better crisping, browning without added steam) that BlueStar owners depend on. When the fan fails, the oven still heats but results change noticeably. We test fan speed and blade integrity on every BlueStar oven call.</li>
        <li><strong>Custom Powder-Coat Finish</strong> — BlueStar's 750+ color options are powder-coat applied to steel panels. Powder coat is more durable than paint but chips at impact and scratches at abrasive contact. Unlike stainless steel, there's no touch-up for powder coat — a chip requires full panel respray. We apply protective covers before any service work near powder-coat panels and use felt-backed tools for all contact points.</li>
        <li><strong>Cast Iron Grates (Open Design)</strong> — BlueStar's bare cast iron grates — no porcelain coating — can be re-seasoned and are more durable long-term than porcelain-coated alternatives. Cast iron grates collect grease into the seasoning layer, which eventually saturates and flakes. Regular cleaning and periodic re-seasoning extend grate life. LA coastal properties see accelerated rust on insufficiently seasoned grates — we note grate seasoning condition and recommend service protocol on every coastal BlueStar call.</li>
      </ul>
      <div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a1015; border-color:#c8820a; margin-top:0">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#e8a030">🔥 Infrared Broiler — The Repair Nobody Else Does</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">BlueStar's infrared broiler is available on Platinum series ranges and produces a level of searing heat unavailable in any other residential range. Most appliance technicians have never serviced one — they treat it as a standard radiant broiler with a different element. It's not. The ceramic infrared element operates at 3x the temperature of a radiant broiler, the gas circuit has specific pressure requirements, and the ignition system is calibrated for the element's thermal characteristics. We service the BlueStar infrared system as the distinct high-temperature assembly it is.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-block" style="background:#0a0a1a; border-color:#3a7bd5; margin-top:16px">
          <div class="tip-label" style="color:#6aabff">🌊 Coastal BlueStar — Cast Iron Grates + Salt Air</div>
          <div class="tip-text" style="color:#bbb">BlueStar's bare cast iron grates — unlike ZLINE's porcelain-coated grates — can rust at coastal LA properties if not properly maintained. The seasoning layer on cast iron grates provides rust protection, but ocean salt air penetrates inadequately seasoned areas rapidly. Properties in Malibu, Pacific Palisades, and Manhattan Beach should have grate re-seasoning as part of annual BlueStar service. We inspect and document grate seasoning condition on every coastal BlueStar call — rust caught early is resolved with re-seasoning, rust left unchecked requires grate replacement.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">04 — Common Problems</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Most Common BlueStar Failures in Los Angeles</h2>

    <div class="problems-grid">
      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔥 Open Burner Port Blockage</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Grease and food debris reaching the star-shaped burner ports directly — the absence of a sealed cap means debris lands on the ports during cooking. Initially presents as uneven flame (some ports partially blocked) before progressing to no-light. LA cooking styles (wok, high-heat searing) generate more port-blocking debris than moderate cooking. We clean all ports using specific technique for the star-cap geometry on every BlueStar service call.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-open">Open Burner</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔆 Infrared Broiler Element Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Ceramic infrared element thermal fatigue — repeated cycling to 1,500°F+ creates micro-fractures that eventually cause visible cracking and performance loss. The symptom: broiler starts taking longer to reach searing temperature, then eventually fails to reach it. We inspect the element for micro-fracture patterns and test surface temperature before and after any broiler repair to verify full restoration.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-broiler">Infrared Broiler</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌡️ Ultra-Low Simmer Creeping Higher</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Ultra-Low restriction valve wear — the valve that creates the 130 BTU minimum gradually loses its restriction calibration through sustained use. The simmer temperature creeps from 130 BTU toward 200–300 BTU over months. Owners notice that slow braises require more attention than they used to. Ultra-Low valve service (not main gas valve replacement) restores the minimum restriction to factory spec.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🔩 Star-Cap Igniter Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">BlueStar's star-shaped burner cap positions the igniter at a specific geometry for the star configuration — ceramic igniters must be positioned correctly for reliable spark at each port. Coastal LA salt air accelerates ceramic tip corrosion. Generic igniters at incorrect geometry produce weak spark even when new. OEM BlueStar star-cap igniters only — the geometry matters for this specific burner design.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">🌊 Cast Iron Grate Rust (Coastal)</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Inadequate seasoning layer on bare cast iron grates — salt air at coastal properties penetrates the cast iron surface where seasoning is thin or absent. Unlike porcelain-coated grates, BlueStar cast iron grates can be restored with re-seasoning if caught early. Structural rust requires grate replacement. Annual seasoning maintenance at coastal properties prevents this from reaching replacement stage.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-coastal">Coastal LA</span>
      </div>

      <div class="problem-card">
        <div class="problem-title">💨 Convection Fan Bearing Failure</div>
        <div class="problem-cause">Dry heat convection fan bearing wear — the fan motor bearings degrade from sustained use at oven temperatures. LA's dusty environment (especially Valley and hillside properties) contributes to earlier bearing wear. The symptom: grinding or squealing during convection cycles before the fan motor fails. We replace the full fan motor assembly on BlueStar ovens — bearing-only service rarely lasts as long as full motor replacement.</div>
        <span class="problem-tag tag-common">Most Common</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

